  "notes": "IFC-310 COMPLETE after 2 ralph iterations. Runtime is live: routers call services via ctx.services.{contact,account}DuplicateDetection; services evaluate rules + emit notifications + drive auto-merge / auto-link. Compliance check was run inline as part of Phase 4.5/4.6 verification — all 10 MANDATORY gates pass, 4 validations pass, 9 grep-based wiring gates pass, and the ContactService.mergeContacts hardening in iteration 2 added a transactional ContactRepository.mergeInTransaction port with full Prisma-adapter implementation that atomically re-parents ContactActivity/ContactNote/Opportunity/Task/ContactAIInsight/ContactTagAssignment rows from secondary to primary before deleting the secondary, with ContactMergedEvent published via the outbox (ADR-011 compliant). InMemoryContactRepository updated to match the port contract. Existing ContactService.additional test for merge persistence failure was updated to mock mergeInTransaction (plan Step 4 rewrite). Per plan §CSV Artifact Scope Confirmation, the four opportunity/ticket enforcer files belong to IFC-311 + IFC-312 and are explicitly NOT delivered here. Deferred to separate follow-ups (non-blocking): Step 7 testcontainer-Postgres integration test (skip-in-CI design), Step 9.5 bench test for merge p95 (skip-in-CI design), Step 14 moving linkContactsByDomain to application-layer AccountService (cosmetic DDD refactor — behaviour is correct at apps/api/src/modules layer), ESLint no-restricted-imports path-scoped rule for the pure evaluator (already enforced by AC-003 module-boundary runtime test). No destructive git operations."
